social_posts.post_text: Hope everyone is having happy holidays ✨

How the move has been going/ 

In case you missed my last reel I now live in nyc and I’m trying to get used to living in a 4th floor walk up 🫠✨

One year ago today Compass picked up my license and three days later I hit the ground running in real estate sales working with a top producing team in Seattle 💃 

After about six months I realized I was in the wrong market and struggled to sell the PNW lifestyle still feeling like my dream was to move to New York. So I finally did it, I picked up my life and moved it to the east coast as most of you know by now. What most people don’t know though (unless you keep up with my YouTube channel) is that I went back to school for my NY real estate license last summer and as I post this today I am over the moon to finally share that I’m currently in the process of hanging my new license with Corcoran 😍 

I’m so grateful to my first team and all the people who spent time to mentor me along the way. As well as the people that just shared their support and encouragement. I wouldn’t have had the guts to move my business to NYC if it wasn’t for those conversations and experiences. More updates to come 🌆
First content dump of the year ✨
SXSW was a vibe and so was Austin 🤠
march dump 💫
The weekend ft @heather_roams :)
April in NYC where some days felt like summer, some felt like spring and sometimes it just rained all day 🌼

This one goes out to ms Safari who has lived many chapters of life with me; nearly every place I stayed in LA and the two years I lived in Seattle. 

Sometimes I’ve wondered if she would have been happy in my tiny NYC studio, if she would have liked sitting in the window watching the birds play on my fire escape. 

Ultimately I felt the flight alone would have been too much for her though which is why she stayed home. Found out my little queen has cancer now so it’s looking like goodbyes will be in order soon. I’m v grateful for my fam who has been looking after her since I moved 🤍
Experiencing life with an open heart is dope 💙
May was weird 🍝

Stoked for my latest client who moved into his first NYC apartment last wknd!

In the heat of the rental market with bidding wars galore, I’m delighted to share that I found my client a hidden gem in Soho, no bidding over necessary. 

I love working with people who move here for the first time as someone who made that same trek cross country by myself. If you know someone relocating to NYC whether they’re looking to buy or rent, your referral would mean the world to me and I would be honored to take care of them 💃📦🗝️🌆
mini June dump 🔮

Sis was in town so we shot some fun content, swipe for a preview of a lil video I put together 💫 My sister is an aspiring photographer based in Seattle so hope you’ll keep her in mind for any of your photo project needs (she loves to travel). This was filmed by both of us @carmanscandids and edited by me - you can watch the full video on YouTube by clicking “your sign to move to nyc” link in my bio 🔮

Trying something new! Going to start sharing my favs around NYC so you can enjoy them too 🌞 

I always wanted to do this when I lived in LA and again when I lived in Seattle but couldn’t figure out how I wanted to do it or find the time so I’m excited to finally start while I’m still kind of fresh to New York 🌆 Swipe for my go to coffee shop at the moment @lacabracoffee 

Located in both the East Village and Soho, I highly recommend their iced matcha latte and literally any of their pastries. You can’t go wrong but the orange danish (pictured) is to die for 🍊 + yes there are vegan options!!
I’m never this person but wow July really came and went. Here’s a lil dump that includes some favs

I’m so happy for one of my recent clients who has been settling into her new UES apartment!! 

After seven showings not only did we find her a quiet oasis to call home but we found a special friendship in each other as well which is one of the many reasons I loooove what I do!

If you know someone looking to rent, buy or sell in nyc, your referral would mean the world to me ✨💃🔑🌆💫
life lately

Long dayyy from picking up documents bright and early, to camping out at a coffee shop until meeting @kkbpgs to go over a purchase application and other client needs to listing photos for a new UES home we’re bringing on soon. 

To ending with a lil sweet treat at @patisserievanessa down the street. Heart full and grateful to be busy this summer doing what I love 💗💗💗
hbd to my long distance bestie 🤍

A work lately post before I’m away for a few days//

-two new contracts as of last night 
-in the process of picking out virtual staging with @kkbpgs for our latest listing coming soon to the UES
-wrapping up another board package

-and feeling grateful to be working with a lovely referral that came from Seattle. If you or someone you know is looking to purchase or sell there or anywhere for that matter, I would love to match you with a fantastic agent!

DM me your email for the full Manhattan/Brooklyn market reports and I promise not to spam :)

August ~

A healthy balance of working, refreshing my goals, relaxing, day dreaming, getting away and spending time with special humans! A few fun ideas/dreams are resurfacing that I’m stoked about and will share as they progress :)

Best times with one of my favorite humans @brandonhoshaw who surprised me with a spontaneous visit this weekend ~ heart feeling so full 

I can’t believe we fit so much in including catching a glimpse of the Animal Liberation March in Soho yesterday

James Cromwell was there who is not only an actor but a known animal rights advocate. He said a few words and then poured red liquid on the sidewalk directly in front of the Louis Vuitton flagship store to make a point that LVMH still uses real fur to this day. It was really beautiful being surrounded by so many passionate people who are using their voices to raise awareness around something many of us likely don’t think about or quite frankly know about 🤍
Best times playing tourist w/ mama, now she’s on her way to JFK and I’m holding back tears so I can work! Byee
Finally got an umbrella in September (thx mom)

flying home with a very full heart 🤍 
looking forward to getting back to the city to hustle and continue to prep my business for next year before coming back to the west coast for the next wave of holidays. swipe to slide seven for my latest tattoo inspo :)
some highs and lows in november

A little over a year ago I sold my mom’s house which was a really special experience. I was reflecting on that time and how amazing it is that she was able to change her whole life with the sale of that home. 

Single mama, living in mountains of credit card debt was able to take 17 years of equity and pay that mortgage off, along with her debt and finally relocate to the state of her dreams to live in the sun with money left to not only enjoy but for a down payment on a new home. 

One of the many reasons homeownership is so cool, one of the many reasons I love building this business 🌞
Shout out to my fam for a mostly drama free holiday and @tiaroachtravels for helping book this trip!!!
cheers to any excuse to reminisce ✨
the last of 2023 ✨ happy new year friends!!
